## TEMA 5 — Flujo en Tuberías

### Darcy-Weisbach
$$H_r = f \cdot \frac{L}{D} \cdot \frac{v^2}{2g}$$

$$\Delta p = f \cdot \frac{L}{D} \cdot \frac{\rho v^2}{2}$$

### Número de Reynolds
$$Re = \frac{\rho v D}{\mu} = \frac{v D}{\nu}$$

Laminar:
$$Re < 2300$$
Turbulento:
$$Re > 4000$$

### Factor de Fricción

Laminar:
$$f = \frac{64}{Re}$$

Turbulento liso
(Blasius,
$$Re < 10^5$$):
$$f = \frac{0.316}{Re^{0.25}}$$

Turbulento general
(Colebrook-White,
implícita):
$$\frac{1}{\sqrt{f}} = -2 \log\left(\frac{\varepsilon/D}{3.71} + \frac{2.51}{Re\sqrt{f}}\right)$$

Swamee-Jain
(explícita):
$$f = \frac{0.25}{\left[\log\left(\frac{\varepsilon/D}{3.71} + \frac{5.74}{Re^{0.9}}\right)\right]^2}$$

### Pérdidas Singulares
$$H_{r,s} = K \cdot \frac{v^2}{2g}$$

### Tuberías en Serie
$$H_{r,\text{total}} = \sum_{i} H_{r,i}$$
$$Q = \text{cte}$$

### Tuberías en Paralelo
$$Q_{\text{total}} = \sum_{i} Q_i$$
$$\Delta H_i = \text{igual en cada rama}$$

